(24, 189, '32', '32', 'Khmer', 'Buddhism', 'Good', '.', '<p>Technical training<br>\r\n	 Microsoft Office (Word, Excel and Power Point)<br>\r\n	 Adobe Photoshop CS3 and Adobe Illustrator CS4<br>\r\n	 Open Office (Writer, Calc and Impress)<br>\r\n	 Internet and E-mail Training courses<br>\r\n	 Computer General Knowledge, Maintenance, Troubleshooting, and Network cabling,<br>\r\n	Network Basic Configuration, Network Infrastructure<br>\r\n	 Microsoft Operating Systems (Window 98, Window 2000 Advanced Server,<br>\r\n	Window ME, Windows XP and Windows Server 2003)<br>\r\n	 Installation and configuration (DNS,DHCP,DHCP Relay Agent, Routing and Remote<br>\r\n	Access, Active directory and user permissions, WINS Server, Ipsec , File server )<br>\r\n	 Linux System administration Installation (SUSE Enterprise.10.0, Ubuntu Server,<br>\r\n	Open SUSE)<br>\r\n	 Linux Configuration ( DNS , DHCP, Mail Server, Samba, Proxy Server, FTP Server,<br>\r\n	Webmin, Joomla, Moodle, OpenLDAP, Nagios, Ntop, Cacti )<br>\r\n	 Cisco networking (CCNA1, CCNA2,CCNA3, and CCNA4), Configure routers and Switch<br>\r\n	(VLAN, STP, VTP, Trunking, Port Security, RIP, EIGRP, OSPF, Static Route, Default<br>\r\n	Route, NAT, PAT,ACL, Frame Relay, )<br>\r\n	 General knowledge about IT security<br>\r\n	 Printers and Scanners ( Install printers and Print server, Share Printers, Install<br>\r\n	Scanners)<br>\r\n	 Install and Configure ISA server 2004 and 2006</p>\r\n', '<p>WORK EXPERIENCE</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br>\r\n	<b>January 2013 till Now, IT &amp; Marketing Design Manager at Comme &agrave; la Maison</b><br>\r\n	I`m in charged following duties:<br>\r\n	 Schedule and control team employees working hours<br>\r\n	 Evaluate, train and develop Assistant<br>\r\n	 Train Assistant to train PC / IT users; employees and customers<br>\r\n	 Control on site if training have been fully understood and implemented<br>\r\n	 Discipline when team employees don&rsquo;t follow regulations and or duties<br>\r\n	 Edit user notice in English, train users<br>\r\n	 Report when users do not follow IT rules and process<br>\r\n	 Recruit new team employees<br>\r\n	 Control setting safety, security and hygiene of equipments and users through<br>\r\n	execution of standards and guidelines<br>\r\n	 Control security of data; set process, firewall, AntiVirus, Back up...through execution<br>\r\n	of standards and guidelines, control the correct use by all users.<br>\r\n	 Configure and control firewall Mickrotik<br>\r\n	 Backup and Maintenance Window Server 2008 ( AD, DNS, DHCP, File Server)<br>\r\n	 Support Users computers, printers, scanners problem<br>\r\n	 Control internet connection and monitoring<br>\r\n	 Configure PABX Systems<br>\r\n	 Create GPO for company users<br>\r\n	 Block website or allow on firewall<br>\r\n	 Control Camera Security<br>\r\n	 Set permission and control File Server ( Window server 2008)<br>\r\n	 Check update anti-virus ( Symantic End Poin deploy to client)<br>\r\n	 Block USB or some software<br>\r\n	 IT network Troubleshooting<br>\r\n	 Wireless Configuration<br>\r\n	 Video conference configuration<br>\r\n	 Design network infrastructure<br>\r\n	 Set up &amp; Control VPN Connections<br>\r\n	 Graph bandwidth monitoring<br>\r\n	 Set up and control POS software for Bakery shops<br>\r\n	 Set up and build POS software for Restaurants<br>\r\n	 Control customer&rsquo;s orders: quality, quantity, and timing. Ensure equipments and<br>\r\n	services meets company standards and customer satisfaction is maintained<br>\r\n	 Respond to users requesting assistance, taking appropriate actions to solve problems<br>\r\n	 Maintain equipment, manage emergency and preventive maintenance<br>\r\n	 Coordinate with Housekeeping and Maintenance according operations needs<br>\r\n	 Control equipment inventory including equipment for catering in &amp; out<br>\r\n	 Control purchase request before validation.<br>\r\n	 Control purchased items /equipment, quantities, quality