(111, 'JOB-109', 21, 44, 28, 9, 22, 4, 2, 8, 'Financial Consultant', '', '13', 2, '18~ 45', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 08:47:55', '<p>JOB TITLE : Financial Consultant<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Senior Business Development Manager<br>\r\n	DEPARTMENT : Sales and Distributions<br>\r\n	LOCATION :<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	សាខាស្រុកបរសេត (កំពង់ស្ពឺ)&nbsp;<br>\r\n	សាខាស្រុកពញ្ញក្រែក (កំពង់ចាម)<br>\r\n	សាខាស្រុកអូររាំងអៅ (កំពង់ចាម)&nbsp;<br>\r\n	សាខាស្រុកស្គន់ (កំពង់ចាម)&nbsp;<br>\r\n	សាខាស្រុកព្រៃឈរ (កំពង់ចាម)&nbsp;<br>\r\n	ៀឧត្តរមានជ័យ<br>\r\n	សាខាស្រុកពួក (បាត់ដំបង)<br>\r\n	ភ្នំពេញ សៀមរាប។<br>\r\n	Job Responsibilities:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Approach potential customers from the customer contact list and referrals provided by a distribution partner&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Present and provide consultation with regards to the life insurance products to all prospected customers and then sell the products as per the needs of such customers<br>\r\n	- Assist the customers by providing them after sales service and information as and when required by such customers&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Work with the Senior Sales Supervisor in providing the regular sales reports as per the Company policies<br>\r\n	- Perform other tasks as required by Supervisor</p>\r\n', '<p>Key Success Factors:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Graduates, from University/College, an advantage.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Fresh graduates with high academic credentials shall be considered, though a field in sales, marketing, banking and finance are preferable.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Experience in sales of 6 &ndash; 12 months would be advantageous&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Result &ndash;oriented, committed, flexibility, and self- driven individuals<br>\r\n	- Good communication skills &amp; negotiation skills<br>\r\n	- Enjoy meeting new people and good relationship management&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Basic computer literacy (MS Word/Excel, Internet, E-mail) is essential<br>\r\n	- Good English would be an additional advantage</p>\r\n', '<p>The Company offers a competitive remuneration package and attractive long term career prospect and a professional, transparent, and exciting environment.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	If you&rsquo;re interested and think you&rsquo;re the right person, please submit your CV with cover letter and a recent photo (4x6) to HR Department by using the contact detail below:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Website: www.prudential.com.kh&nbsp;<br>\r\n	Email: pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	Cc: rathana.hout@prudential.com.kh;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Phone: 023 964 555<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Deadline: No later than 01 March, 2017 at 5:30PM<br>\r\n	Women and the disabled are encouraged to apply. Only short-listed candidates will be notified for interview. Received applications will not be returned.<br>\r\n	Notes: Certificates and supporting documents attached should be brought along when you are invited for interview.</p>\r\n', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-10', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(112, 'JOB-112', 21, 44, 32, 9, 22, 4, 2, 8, 'Supervisor – Legal & Corporate Integrity', '', 'Many', 2, '18~ 45', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 08:50:47', '<p>Direct Reporting Line: Senor Supervisor-Legal and Corporate Integrity<br>\r\n	Department/Function: Finance<br>\r\n	Work Location: Phnom Penh, Cambodia<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Principle Accountabilities:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Assist to develop the policy and Standard of Procedures to be in line with Group, Regional, and other applicable regulatory requirements, to cover money laundering deterrence issues, to protect the good reputation of the Group and avoid criminal and civil sanctions against the company, or its employees including analyzing and quarterly updating AML risk assessment;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Administer Customer Risk Classification System where this role will capture customers with higher risk profile in respect of money laundering, terrorism financing and sanctions so that business can be proceed per business as usual in accordance with Group, Regional Head Office, and PCLA risk appetite;<br>\r\n	&bull; Source independent information to build up case for verification of alerts from Sanctions Screening which provide significant supports to Operations, in particular New Business and Underwriting, through fast tracking the turnaround time for policy issuance;<br>\r\n	&bull; Clear initial screening and monthly screening alerts and provide the related assistance to other departments on as needed basis;<br>\r\n	&bull; Report the Suspicious Transaction Reporting (&ldquo;STR&rdquo;) and Cash Transaction Reporting (&ldquo;CTR&rdquo;) to Cambodian Financial Intelligence Unit (&ldquo;CAFIU&rdquo;). STR and CTR are required every two (02) weeks to ensure that the business is conducted in compliance with the local requirements;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Update Local Political Exposed Persons List and Local Sanction List;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Evaluate new products and services to determine the level of risk 1) conduct the new customer by KYC/CDD before acceptance; 2) Evaluate the risk assessment of customers by level of risks; 3) Monitor the existing customers regularly;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Prepare and submit reports as required under local regulations and PCA/Group standards such as AML Quarterly Report and AML Annual Risk Assessment;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Monitor transactions and prepare suspicious transactions report as per company policy<br>\r\n	&bull; Conduct standard monitoring and special monitoring as required per plan<br>\r\n	&bull; Work with IT Department to enhance &amp; develop the AML Profiling in in Life Asia System as per compliance plan<br>\r\n	&bull; Prepare the recommendation and report re the result of AML screening for MLPO review and sign-off<br>\r\n	&bull; Be a contact person with AML Regional Team and prepare and update policies and procedures based on updated Group and Regional policy and disseminate information to the relevant personnel, can be through email or training<br>\r\n	&bull; Oversee administrative matters related to and compliance with anti-money laundering and terrorist financing activities<br>\r\n	&bull; Develop quality assurance (QA) review template and perform QA review according to the approved annual work plans to ensure procedures and policies are effectively implemented<br>\r\n	&bull; Follow up the QA findings in regular basis to ensure the compliance risk can be closed in timeliness by tracking report<br>\r\n	&bull; Be a contact person/coordinator with Regional AML/GWIA team when they conduct QA review/audit review<br>\r\n	&bull; Changing the attitudes of management &amp; staff in relation to AML &amp; CFT<br>\r\n	&bull; Be able to identify and assess AML/CFT related risks as per business scope<br>\r\n	&bull; Develop &amp; review AML Training Materials (induction training) either through video training, CBT platform, or face to face training and make sure the training material is up to date based on the revised policies<br>\r\n	&bull; Provide necessary AML training whenever required<br>\r\n	&bull; Be a helpful assistant/adviser re AML matters to all functions in the Company whenever the help is needed<br>\r\n	&bull; If required, cooperate with internal investigator (local or regional level), to investigate all AML related cases</p>\r\n', '<p>Qualification:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- University graduated, major in Law, Economics, Business Administration, Accounting, or Finance&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Experience in legal, compliance, finance, banking, auditing, distribution channel or equivalents is desired&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Possess Research Skills, Reporting Research Results, Analyzing Information, Coordination, Administrative Writing Skills, and Organization, Working with others, Audit, General Math Skills, And Statistical Analysis.<br>\r\n	- Excellent spoken and written English<br>\r\n	- At least four years of relevant experiences<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Desirable:<br>\r\n	- Has a strong ability to apply logical and critical thinking to resolve problems<br>\r\n	- Propensity to plan strategically yet be able to adapt quickly to reality&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Strong analytical skills<br>\r\n	- Strong numerical, written, and verbal communication skills<br>\r\n	- Ability to build trust and rapport with all levels of the organization<br>\r\n	- Good communication &amp; strong commitment in performing all tasks</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-10', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(113, 'JOB-113', 21, 44, 29, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Customer Service Officer', '1', 'Many', 2, '18~ 45', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 08:52:47', '<p>JOB TITLE : Customer Service Officer<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Senior Executive &ndash; Customer Service<br>\r\n	DEPARTMENT : Operations and IT<br>\r\n	LOCATION : Siem Reap<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	PURPOSE OF THE ROLE<br>\r\n	- To serve and fulfil the needs of walk-in customers and agents including refer to them to sales desk, process/collect premium (where sales is made at the sales desk) as well as dealing with walk-in customers and agents.<br>\r\n	Job Responsibilities<br>\r\n	- Handle simple complaints and enquiries from walk-in customers and agents and ensure that all pending, complex cases and complaints are escalated to supervisor/manager and relevant sections and follow-up promptly<br>\r\n	- Collect premiums (initial and renewal) from customers and agents&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Receive and check requests of policy alterations e.g. address, telephone number, policy profiles etc.<br>\r\n	- Attend to and fulfil policy enquiries by customers and persuade customers to remain their policies<br>\r\n	- Receive documents for claims and others from customers or agents.<br>\r\n	- Identify sales lead and refer customers or sales lead to the appropriate frontline sales e.g. sales desk, life insurance specialist (LIS) or agents<br>\r\n	- Perform other duties as required by the Senior Executive/Supervisor</p>\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;A fresh graduate with at least 01 year experience in customer service and/or receptionist<br>\r\n	- Positive attitude, self-starter, independent, detail oriented and well-organized<br>\r\n	- Maintain a professional behaviour when dealing with customers<br>\r\n	- Ability and accuracy of work and cash handling<br>\r\n	- Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Internet, and Email.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Good in English and Khmer both spoken and written<br>\r\n	- Excellent communication skills<br>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-10', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(114, 'JOB-114', 21, 44, 28, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Senior Supervisor - Risk and Compliance', '3', 'Many', 2, '18~ 45', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 08:55:29', '<p>Direct Reporting Line: Head &ndash; Risk and Compliance<br>\r\n	Department/Function: Finance / Risk and Compliance<br>\r\n	Work Location: Phnom Penh, Cambodia<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Job Purpose Statement:<br>\r\n	- Implementing written policies, procedures, and standards of conduct<br>\r\n	- Developing effective lines of communication<br>\r\n	- Enforcing standards through well publicized disciplinary guidelines and developing policies addressing dealings with sanctioned individuals<br>\r\n	- Conducting periodic risk assessments / and response plans<br>\r\n	- Conducting internal monitoring and auditing<br>\r\n	- Responding promptly to detected offenses, developing corrective action, and reporting findings to the management/government (if any)<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Principle Accountabilities:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Review new product, training, marketing materials and other customer-facing materials;<br>\r\n	- Engage with other department in response to regulatory change such as conduct gap analysis, updating RM/RCD etc.<br>\r\n	- Regularly reporting/update line manager on compliance related mater;<br>\r\n	- Assist line manager in producing relevant reports for CEO/CFO/local Risk Committee/Audit Committee/BOD/regional on a timely basis;<br>\r\n	- Assist line manager in reviewing and updating local compliance manual and other SoPs based on change of regulation and group requirements;<br>\r\n	- Assist line manager in reviewing and comment on the relevant first line&rsquo;s SoPs;<br>\r\n	- Conduct compliance induction training to new joiners;<br>\r\n	- Coordinate with Compliance Coordinator in reporting the monthly compliance coordinator report and challenge the Compliance, coordinator where relevant (e.g. remedial actions) and keep track of the agreed actions;<br>\r\n	- Independently investigating and acting on matters related to compliance, including the flexibility to design and coordinate internal investigations (e.g., responding to reports of problems, &#39;hot-line&#39; calls) and suggesting resulting and corrective actions to the SFDC for decision making;<br>\r\n	- Lead in Quality Assurance work to ensure that the applicable laws and regulations are adhered to;<br>\r\n	- Assisting in developing policies and programs that encourage managers and employees to report on compliance related and other improprieties;<br>\r\n	- Compliance advice to internal and other departments;<br>\r\n	- Other tasks as assigned by the Department Head</p>\r\n', '<p>University graduated or equivalent, major in Law, Economics, Business Administration, Accounting, or Finance;<br>\r\n	- Experience in legal, compliance, finance, auditing, distribution channel or equivalents is desired;<br>\r\n	- Possess a Research Skill, Reporting Research Results, Analyzing Information, Coordination, Administrative Writing Skills, Organization, Working with Others, Audit, General Math Skills, and Statistical Analysis;<br>\r\n	- Has a strong ability to apply logical and critical thinking to resolve problems;<br>\r\n	- Propensity to plan strategically yet be able to adapt quickly to reality;<br>\r\n	- Strong analytical skills;<br>\r\n	- Strong numerical, written, and verbal communication skills;<br>\r\n	- Ability to build trust and rapport with all levels of the organization;<br>\r\n	- Excellent spoken and written English;<br>\r\n	- At least 3 years of relevant experiences</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-10', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(115, 'JOB-115', 21, 44, 44, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Supervisor – Contact Center', '', 'Many', 2, '18~ 45', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 08:58:31', '<p>JOB TITLE : Supervisor &ndash; Contact Center<br>\r\n	JOB GRADE : 07<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Manager- Policy Management and Contact Center<br>\r\n	DEPARTMENT : Operations &amp; IT<br>\r\n	LOCATION : Phnom Penh<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Job Mandate:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Quality control on contact center staff performance as well as to do development session of each contact center staff in order to ensure that customers are being served at high level of satisfaction.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Key Accountabilities:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Keep updated on new or enhanced products/information/services in order to maintain a high quality service to Customers<br>\r\n	- No valid complaint on jobholder&rsquo;s performance<br>\r\n	- Contribute to team goals and objectives<br>\r\n	- Call monitoring and performance valuation of each contact center staff<br>\r\n	- Listen to inbound and outbound voice recording of contact center staff<br>\r\n	- Identify the weaknesses of the contact center staff and providing the appropriated training course<br>\r\n	- Provide coaching, supporting and advice to contact center staff when finding any improper practice<br>\r\n	- Produce weekly/ monthly contact center reports to line manager<br>\r\n	- Make sure all complaints are closed within TAT and prepare complaint report for line manager<br>\r\n	- Identify significant complaint and immediately escalate to line manager<br>\r\n	- Upload the call data in daily basis into contact center system (auto call dialing) for making outbound call<br>\r\n	- Other duties as assigned</p>\r\n', '<p>Key Success Factors:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	 Required:<br>\r\n	- Graduate<br>\r\n	- Experience in handling/managing Contact Center<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	 Desirable:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Bachelor, preferably in Engineering, IT&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Experience in supervising Contact Center from telecommunication or banking industry<br>\r\n	 Qualification: Bachelor degree with good Khmer and English (Speaking, reading, listening and writing)<br>\r\n	 Competencies: Positive attitude &amp; spirit, customer oriented. Productivity &amp; efficiency, accuracy of work<br>\r\n	 Knowledge: Quality and reliability of information provided to customers<br>\r\n	 Skills: Very good leadership, Communication and Computer Skills<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	The Company offers a competitive remuneration package and attractive long term career prospective to work in a professional, transparent, exciting and ethical environment for all its staff.</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-08', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(116, 'JOB-116', 21, 44, 32, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Corporate Office and Administration Officer', '', 'Many', 2, '18~ 45', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 09:00:19', '<p>JOB TITLE : Corporate Office and Administration Officer<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Assistant Manager - Customer Service<br>\r\n	DEPARTMENT : Operations and IT<br>\r\n	LOCATION : Phnom Penh, Battambang and Siem Reap Province<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Mandate<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Greets visitors and performs general administrative duties. Handles incoming calls. Also assist other administrative staff with overflow work and their duties requested by Assistant Manager - Office Service and Facility Management. The receptionist should also communicate with staff in a friendly manner.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Roles and Responsibilities<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	 Manages the company&rsquo;s lobby area to ensure that reception area is safe, well cleaned and tidy<br>\r\n	 Greets and directs all visitors, including vendors, clients, job candidates and customers appropriately<br>\r\n	 Maintain security by following procedures: monitoring visitor&rsquo;s log book and visitors&rsquo; cards handling by security guards<br>\r\n	 Handles incoming calls by answering or referring inquiries<br>\r\n	 Assist administrative staff by handling other tasks:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- car booking for staff travelling in town and to province<br>\r\n	- meeting room and training room booking<br>\r\n	- maintain and request stationery and printing supplies (paper, pen, toner, name cards, ID cards, business cards, etc.) for office operations.<br>\r\n	- monitor and make monthly report of stationery requisition (paper and toner, etc.) car booking, electricity consumption comparing from month to moth<br>\r\n	- maintain and monitor all the records of all staff holding the Building Security Pass and office access card (requesting, blocking) and call check in be-annually basic.<br>\r\n	- Involved in Fixed Assets counting and labeling, and monitoring all office cleaning, and pest control<br>\r\n	- Update Staff workstation (staff name, location)<br>\r\n	- Produce complete correct monthly car usage, electricity and stationery tracking report<br>\r\n	- Do other tasks assigned by direct manager<br>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Key Accountabilities:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Direct report to Assistant Manager - Office Service and Facility Management:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	1. Keeps all the records of the stationery and printing supplies in the monthly basic and print out for sign off<br>\r\n	2. Request to purchase stationery and printing supplies for office operation and sales related in the monthly basic<br>\r\n	3. Ensures that the summary records of paper and toner consumption and car usage are made correctly in the monthly basic and available as needs<br>\r\n	4. Ensures that all invoices and incoming/outgoing documents reach recipients as soon as possible<br>\r\n	5. Contribute to team effort by accomplishing related result as needs<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Key Success Factors:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	 Qualifications: Bachelor graduate<br>\r\n	 Competencies: Positive attitude &amp; Spirit<br>\r\n	 Skills: Telephone Skills, verbal communication, listening professionalism, customer focus, informing others, handles pressure and supply management.<br>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-10', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(117, 'JOB-117', 21, 44, 29, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Contact Center Officer', '', '3', 2, '', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 09:04:54', '<p>JOB TITLE : Contact Center Officer<br>\r\n	NUMBER REQURIED : 03<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Supervisor - Contact Center Officer<br>\r\n	DEPARTMENT : Operations and IT<br>\r\n	LOCATION : Phnom Penh<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Key Accountabilities:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Customer First:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	 Provide friendly and responsive customer service on the phone to both internal and external customers by using excellent customer service standard and skills<br>\r\n	 Answer customer enquiries on the phone relative to products, procedures, renewal premium date, or refer to<br>\r\n	appropriate area for action<br>\r\n	 Handling customer complaints or refer them to appropriate area for action<br>\r\n	 Accurately identifying a customer&rsquo;s query and providing a quick resolution, first call solution<br>\r\n	 Undertake out-bound call work such as &ldquo;Welcome Call, and Premium reminder&rdquo; and other customer&rsquo;s call Customer Service Standards:<br>\r\n	 Using Prudential Welcome phrase<br>\r\n	 Friendly and Professional answering and asking customer questions<br>\r\n	 Address customer appropriately (use customer name)<br>\r\n	 Complete requested &amp; ask if the customer has any additional needs<br>\r\n	 Keeping the customer up to date with the progress of any escalated enquiries<br>\r\n	 Thank customer and farewell to customer using their name<br>\r\n	 Selling of additional products and functionality where possible to the advantage of the customer<br>\r\n	 Other duties as assigned<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Perform (Well-managed)<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	 Promptly and accurately complete all related administration activities: update customer&rsquo;s information, welcome call and premium reminder report&hellip;..<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	 Monitoring and actively managing variances from agreed performance targets, through identifying and understanding the causes and taking corrective action to minimize risk and maximize performance<br>\r\n	 Ensure compliance with Prudential policies and procedures and local statutory requirements to minimize any potential loss to Prudential<br>\r\n	 Ensure enquires are answered promptly and correctly, reducing any potential loss that may arise from incorrectly processed items and any subsequent claims<br>\r\n	 Take ownership of your continuing professional development, documenting your development plan and tracking your development<br>\r\n	 Contribute honest and direct feedback to line manager on potential service/process enhancements, what is going well, and where team improvement is possible<br>\r\n	 Identify sales lead and customer referral to appropriate frontline sales, e.g sale desk, LIC, and LIS</p>\r\n', '<p>Excellent in English. Other languages are an advantage<br>\r\n	- Strong Customer Service skills, commitment and a desire to satisfy the customer<br>\r\n	- Good listening and problem solving skills<br>\r\n	- Previous telephone experience in handling customer calls<br>\r\n	- Skills in supporting business development planning, documentation and implementation<br>\r\n	- High-level analytical skills with the ability to think laterally and the flexibility to be able to work in an environment of change.<br>\r\n	- General PC literacy and keyboard skills<br>\r\n	- Demonstrated high level interpersonal and communication skills (particularly with regards to telephone etiquette)<br>\r\n	- Thorough knowledge of bank procedures, products and services<br>\r\n	- Willing to work shifts as required</p>\r\n', '<p>If you&rsquo;re interested and think you&rsquo;re the right person, please submit your CV with cover letter and&nbsp;a recent photo (4x6)&nbsp;to<br>\r\n	HR Department by using the contact detail below:<br>\r\n	Website:&nbsp;www.prudential.com.kh<br>\r\n	Email:&nbsp;pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh<br>\r\n	Phone: 023 964 555<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Deadline: No later than&nbsp;06 December 2016 at 5:30PM<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Phnom Penh Address:&nbsp;Phnom Penh Tower, 20F, #445 Monivong Blvd, Boeung Prolit, 7 Makara, Phnom Penh, Kingdom of Cambodia<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Women and the disabled are encouraged to apply. Only short-listed candidates will be notified for interview.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Received applications will not be returned.<br>\r\n	Notes: Certificates and supporting documents attached should be brought along when you are invited for interview.</p>\r\n', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-10', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(118, 'JOB-118', 21, 44, 35, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Assistant - New Business', '', '', 2, '', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 09:06:42', '<p>JOB TITTLE : Assistant - New Business<br>\r\n	JOB GRADE : Level 4<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Supervisor - New Business<br>\r\n	FUNCTION/DEPARTMENT : OP and IT<br>\r\n	LOCATION : Prudential Cambodia Life Assurance (PCLA), Phnom Penh<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Job Mandate:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Is responsible for handling and managing the flows and movement of physical proposal files between and among various members of NBUW and CS to ensure that the files are in order and easy to locate while the proposals are being created in LAS and underwritten. The job holder is also responsible in assisting the NB team in packing the policy kits.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Key Responsibilities:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	1. Handling and recording the movement of physical proposal files between and among various member of NBUW and CS to ensure a smooth flows of the work;<br>\r\n	2. Locate and pass on the physical proposal files to relevant staff as requested;<br>\r\n	3. Check and reconcile the physical proposal files or pending files on a regular basis as agreed with Supervisor to ensure that they match with the soft proposal files;<br>\r\n	4. Arrange the physical closed proposal files e.g. approval or decline and transfer them to the image team for further archiving<br>\r\n	5. Other duties as assigned by the Supervisor and/or NBUW management.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Key Accountabilities:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Direct report to Executive, Imaging and Document Admin.:<br>\r\n	1. Properly and accurately manage the movement of physical proposal files between and among member of NBUW and CS;<br>\r\n	2. Timely locate and pass on the physical proposal files to relevant staff as requested;<br>\r\n	3. Physical proposal files are properly recorded, updated and reconciled on regular basis &ndash; no file is missing;<br>\r\n	4. Arrange the physical closed proposal files and pass them on to Image and Doc team within the agreed TAT</p>\r\n', '<p>Key Success Factors:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	1. Qualifications: At lease high school graduate with good English in addition to Khmer<br>\r\n	- Some prior experience in filing and mail delivery works<br>\r\n	- Basic knowledge of computer office applications e.g. Word, Excel etc.<br>\r\n	2. Competencies: Customer and details oriented and be sensitive to and ability to maintain crucial customer information in the strictest confidentiality.<br>\r\n	4. Skills: Good communication, resilient and ability to work longer hours from time to time</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-08', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(119, 'JOB-119', 21, 44, 33, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'HR Executive - Reward', '2', '', 2, '', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English', '2017-03-15', '2017-02-08 09:08:18', '<p>JOB TITLE : HR Executive - Reward<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Manager &ndash; Compensation &amp; Benefits<br>\r\n	DEPARTMENT : Human Resources<br>\r\n	LOCATION : Phnom Penh<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Job Mandate:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	To assist overall administration of Compensation and Benefits function in the HR department<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Main Tasks &amp; Job Responsibilities:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Administer employee exit process both LIS &amp; Non LIS<br>\r\n	- Verify candidates&rsquo; documents prior to on-boarding process<br>\r\n	- Issue employment contracts to LIS<br>\r\n	- Manage LIS personnel files<br>\r\n	- Provide LIS payroll support<br>\r\n	- Administer all local employee benefits<br>\r\n	- Act as the second in-charge of Senior HR Executive</p>\r\n', '<p>A graduate from relevant disciplines<br>\r\n	- At least 2 years of experience admin work<br>\r\n	- Excellent English and Khmer language skills<br>\r\n	- Excellent interpersonal skills<br>\r\n	- Team player and well-organized<br>\r\n	- High level of integrity<br>\r\n	- Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-02-08', '2017-03-10', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
