(151, 'JOB-151', 121, 20, 45, 9, 45, 4, 2, 7, 'Flight Coordinating Agent (01 position)', '.', '1', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-18', '2017-03-18 17:09:22', '<p>* Department: Ground Handling<br>\r\n	* Location: Phnom Penh International Airport<br>\r\n	* General Responsibilities:<br>\r\n	- Be responsible for coordinating all activities with Ramp Side&rsquo;s personnel at aircraft, Operating Passenger Boarding Bridge (PBB), filing flight plan, editing any operational messages, and providing all necessary information or available documentation of the flights to airlines and/or cockpit crews;<br>\r\n	- Be responsible for performing the tasks of load sheet after being trained and been qualified by airlines and/or aircraft types;<br>\r\n	- Be responsible for checking ramp area including Foreign Object Damage (FOD) and anything that may obstruct the parking of aircraft.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Working Conditions:<br>\r\n	- Working on shift (flexible working schedule rotating within 24h/7d);<br>\r\n	- Wearing Uniform and individual safety equipment;<br>\r\n	- Subject to Security/Safety certification prior to the employment</p>\r\n', '<p>- Cambodia nationality and legal age;<br>\r\n	- Minimum Bachelor Degree and Majoring in IT is a plus;<br>\r\n	- Experiences in Airport Services Activity is a plus;<br>\r\n	- Proficiency in both speaking and writing in Khmer and English, knowledge of any other languages are an advantage;<br>\r\n	- Good knowledge in mathematics;<br>\r\n	- Good knowledge in computer skills (Microsoft Offices, Internet &amp; Email, Database etc.&hellip;.);<br>\r\n	- Ability to work under pressure with less supervision;<br>\r\n	- Good inter-personal skill, confident and motivated person;<br>\r\n	- Physically and mentally fit and can-do- attitude.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	* Deadline: 24 th March 2017 by 5:00 p.m.<br>\r\n	* Interested applicants should submit CV and cover letter to: Phnom Penh International Airport Administrative Building PO Box 1256