(249, 'JOB-249', 143, 50, 31, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Brand Executive', '3', '.', 1, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Fair   ', '2017-04-12', '2017-03-22 17:07:48', '<p>** Role Purpose:<br>\r\n	1. Drives customer messaging and communications plan to strengthen engagement and brand value. Supporting brand components and measurement approach.<br>\r\n	2. Defines business objectives to advance customer-facing brand properties.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	3. Ensures delivery of direct-to-customer communications in a consistent brand voice either through direct development or template creation.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	4. Support Brand Manager<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Assist Brand Manager in developing marketing activities and plan for the market&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Execute marketing activities, keep monitoring and do the evaluation&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Effectively coordinate with all stakeholders/ agencies/ suppliers to ensure the on-time delivery of marketing activities/ marketing materials on time and in full&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Assist Brand Manager in generating creative/ supplier brief for creative design/ points of sales materials in line with brand strategies&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Assist Brand Manager in preparing assigned report/ presentation on regular basis&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Budget management: Keep well control on the yearly/ monthly marketing expenditures and regularly report on the incurred budget spend vs. plan<br>\r\n	- Conduct market visit and make report as job required&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Candidate Minimum Requirements:<br>\r\n	- The jobholder requires a business degree or equivalent academic qualification.<br>\r\n	- Minimum 3 years working experience in advertising agency/multi-national companies.<br>\r\n	- Challenging and outgoing - Strong in interpersonal skill<br>\r\n	- Be able to work under pressure<br>\r\n	- Strong communication, creative and strategic thinking skill<br>\r\n	- Well spoken and written English and Khmer<br>\r\n	- Be able to travel to provinces as job required&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Strong analytical skill&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Ability to understand research methodology (i.e.: concept/ design testing, Quan/ Qaul research) is a plus</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-22', '2017-04-21', 'HR Department', '086 888 251', 'recruitment@kh.imptob.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(250, 'JOB-250', 143, 50, 33, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Talent Executive', '2', '.', 1, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Fair   ', '2017-04-12', '2017-03-22 17:12:27', '<p>** Role Purpose:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- To support the Human Resources Manager by ensuring the effective and efficient implementation of HR process aimed at delivering the appropriate staff recruitment, training and development and performance management, OHSE strategy in line with business context and organization requirements<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	HR Operations &amp; Employee Relations<br>\r\n	- Support HR Manager to implement the HR cycle including Recruitment, Training Calendar Development, and Integrated Performance Management (IPM) Process<br>\r\n	- Maintain the HR database, ensure the data accuracy and ensure that all users&rsquo; data are up to date and backup properly.<br>\r\n	- Support HR Manager in the execution of Engagement Survey and Engagement follow up initiatives<br>\r\n	- To promote and manage company-wide Engagement Programs and other Employee Relations / communication activities.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Coordinate and administer monthly headcount reporting, staff movement, organization chart, and statistics. Reports are submitted on time and accurate<br>\r\n	- Work closely with C&amp;B Supervisor to ensure new joiner and leaver process are duly followed for HR compliance purpose, and all records (including interview assessment sheet, new hire personnel data, insurance enrollment, and exit interview record) are kept intact for all level of employee<br>\r\n	- Collaborate with HR team to support and drive overall HR agenda and perform other tasks as required<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Recruitment&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Coordinate and administer the recruitment and selection process. Ensure adherence to governance, best practice and processes throughout the selection process, drive the on-boarding process, liaise with and monitor the recruitment agency.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Develop and manage the Imperial Tobacco employer brand, working closely with HR Manager and Brand Team to build, expand and strengthen the Imperial Tobacco employer brand proposition both internally and externally.<br>\r\n	- To ensure company&rsquo;s onboarding programs are in place and full implemented.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Training<br>\r\n	- Coordinate and implement Learning and Development plan. Work with HR Manager to identify capabilities gap and support general competency development through in-house or external training initiatives, and maintain up-to-date training records.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Follow up on &ldquo;after-training&rdquo; action plans implementation and related Development plans amendments if needed (both with trained staff and line managers)<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	OTHER<br>\r\n	- To ensure Occupational, Health, Safety and Environment program are implemented and align with the Group guideline<br>\r\n	- Conduct communication sessions to cascade the OHSE new update<br>\r\n	- Assist HR Manager to run Safety observations and near miss reporting</p>\r\n', '<p>- Candidate Minimum Requirements: (Qualifications, Languages, etc...)<br>\r\n	- University degree in Business Management or related business field<br>\r\n	- 2-3 years experiences in HR or Administration in a multinational company<br>\r\n	- Knowledge of recruitment/ hiring processes<br>\r\n	- Business understanding of all other functions and their interaction with HR<br>\r\n	- Good inter-personal and communication skills</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-22', '2017-04-21', 'HR Department', '086 888 251', 'recruitment@kh.imptob.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(251, 'JOB-251', 145, 47, 52, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Stock Controller & Purchasing Order', '2', '1', 0, '24 ~ 35', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Excellent   ', '2017-04-07', '2017-03-24 13:39:40', '<p>- Check and delivery product to store<br>\r\n	- Organizing stocks, uniforms on shelves and store rooms<br>\r\n	- Involved in Purchasing, Receiving, Physical Counting, Processing Daily Paperwork and Form<br>\r\n	- Prepare reports on adjustments to inventories, spoiled, damaged, technical<br>\r\n	- Reconciliation of Reports (Warehouse Stock out, Stock in and Balance and product has problem, product booking)<br>\r\n	- Prepare daily and monthly report of stock<br>\r\n	- Check stock available in system<br>\r\n	- Check Physical stock where the location is<br>\r\n	- Count Physical stock is available&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Arrange new item by put into a right position in our warehouse<br>\r\n	- Create new code or new ID for new item<br>\r\n	- Daily update stock inventories and report to Management<br>\r\n	- Weekly and monthly report to head office<br>\r\n	-Daily stock controlling &ndash;Stock in and Stock out<br>\r\n	-Inventories stock report to Management everyday<br>\r\n	-Manage all inventories in stock<br>\r\n	-Maintaining all proper documents processed for the receipt of goods and supplier<br>\r\n	-Other tasks assigned by directly supervisor Update weekly report to keep filling&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>- Attention to detail and accuracy in numeracy<br>\r\n	- Able to use Microsoft word, Excel and inventory system<br>\r\n	- Reliable, Honest and Responsible for assigned tasks<br>\r\n	- Good computer Skills, Online and Internet<br>\r\n	- Good in analytical thinking<br>\r\n	- High motivation and active person<br>\r\n	- Work under pressure &amp; honest Strong working comment and flexible to work - At least 2 year&rsquo;s experience with stock controller<br>\r\n	-Good computer skills, Microsoft offices (Word, Excel)<br>\r\n	-Hard working person, honesty<br>\r\n	-Be self-confident, self-motivated<br>\r\n	-Able to work overtime</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'FeedPro Recruitment', '+855 106 26821', 'dina.prum@feedpro-kh.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(252, 'JOB-252', 145, 47, 52, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Logistic Operation', '2', '1', 0, '24 ~ 35', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Excellent   ', '2017-04-22', '2017-03-24 13:45:12', '<p>- Making documents to go through the customs formalities<br>\r\n	- Inputting data into a customs system<br>\r\n	- Communication and negotiation with the customs staffs through the customs formalities<br>\r\n	- Logistics operation management in order to move a product from supplier to customer, keep supply chain works correctly to get goods to arrive at the right place, at the right time.<br>\r\n	- Prepare document import and export products<br>\r\n	- Management all product&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Other task assigned by manager</p>\r\n', '<p>- Fluent in English higher than Daily upper level for 4 commands<br>\r\n	- Female only<br>\r\n	- High motivation, polite character<br>\r\n	- Experience Logistics Operations (Import &amp; Export)&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Must know customer declaration&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Good skill English language&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Hardworking and High job responsibility<br>\r\n	- Able to work under pressure<br>\r\n	- Computer skill word, excel ,internet and email<br>\r\n	- Good communication<br>\r\n	- Strong management and leadership skills&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Flexible and good at team work<br>\r\n	- Self-motivate and confident</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'FeedPro Recruitment', '+855 106 26821', 'dina.prum@feedpro-kh.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(253, 'JOB-253', 102, 50, 28, 9, 45, 4, 2, 8, 'Sales Supervisor (Urgent)', '2', '3', 2, '', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-08', '2017-03-24 13:48:08', '<p>- Boost up sale by promote Company products with high efficiency and effectiveness.<br>\r\n	- Identify and approaching target market/customers to sell the products<br>\r\n	- Understanding current and potential customers.<br>\r\n	- Develop the Sales strategy and planning.<br>\r\n	- Preparation for annual sales budgets including propose sales planning.<br>\r\n	- Achieve the target given by the company.<br>\r\n	- Preparation of sales reports.<br>\r\n	- Customer feedback and satisfaction survey.<br>\r\n	- Interacting and building good relationship with customers.<br>\r\n	- Other task as per assigned by the Director from time to time.</p>\r\n', '<p>- Degree in Sales &amp; Marketing or relevant.<br>\r\n	- At least 4 years working experiences in sales and marketing&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Good command of English, good communication and negotiation skill.<br>\r\n	- Proactive and hardworking and possess of positive attitude<br>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'HR', '076-677 8727', 'career.limtan@gmail.com', NULL, 1, 1),
