(303, 'JOB-303', 148, 23, 39, 9, 24, 4, 2, 7, 'Senior Foreign Financial Institutions Officer', '2', '.', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-01', '2017-03-24 17:08:10', '<p>** Job Description<br>\r\n	S/he is totally responsible for sales remittance by coordinate with relationship managers in all ABA branch to improve remittance services and attract new remittance clients to the bank. S/he shall frequently travel to provincial branch and keep good relationship with existing clients.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Location<br>\r\n	Head Office, Phnom Penh<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Periodically review and update the documentation.<br>\r\n	- Respond to AML and other requests of financial institutions.<br>\r\n	- Contact financial institutions by requests of other departments.<br>\r\n	- Keep files of financial institutions.<br>\r\n	- Analyze existing relations and establishing new relations.<br>\r\n	- Lead and prepare the borrowing plan from overseas banks and FIs base on proper analysis on loan requirement with relevant departments.<br>\r\n	- Manage and prepare borrowing documents to ensure there are enough data for submitting to the committee.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;\r\n				<table>\r\n					<tbody>\r\n						<tr>\r\n							<td>-&nbsp;At least 2 year experience in correspondent banking or financial institutions.<br>\r\n								- At least bachelor degree in banking, economics or finance.<br>\r\n								Strong PC user skills.<br>\r\n								- Accuracy and responsibility.<br>\r\n								- Written and oral English is a must.<br>\r\n								- Knowledge of local regulation is a plus.<br>\r\n								- Strong analysis on financial and economic data.<br>\r\n								- Organizational, leadership and time management skills.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.</td>\r\n						</tr>\r\n					</tbody>\r\n				</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'HR Department Office', '855 98 630 108', 'recruitment@ababank.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(304, 'JOB-304', 148, 23, 46, 9, 24, 4, 2, 7, 'Contact Centre Consultant', '.', '.', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-01', '2017-03-24 17:10:08', '<p>** Job Description<br>\r\n	This role is responsible for providing great customer experience by delivering excellent customer service and quality service standard for inbound and outbound calls.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	We realize that our greatest asset is our people. That is why we are creating a unique climate of inspiration, leadership, values and great opportunities that will enable the best in the market to thrive as part of our diverse team.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Location<br>\r\n	- Phnom Penh, Head Office<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	1. Inbound call<br>\r\n	- Respond to customer inquiries by following the customer service standard and script provided by ABA Bank.<br>\r\n	- Research required information using available resources (if assigned by Head of department).<br>\r\n	- Handle/ resolve customer complaints (if doable in your level) and/or Identify and escalate priority issues/complaints to the right person of the units which a complaint/issue raised to.<br>\r\n	- Perform your role and contact point from the client to follow up and close the complaint/issue.<br>\r\n	- Follow‐up customer calls where necessary.<br>\r\n	- Provide customers with product and service information, terms and conditions if asked by the client.<br>\r\n	- Route calls to appropriate departments if a query/complaint is not manageable within your discretion.<br>\r\n	- Complete call logs and prepare call reports on the timely manner.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	2. Outbound Calls<br>\r\n	- Contact businesses or private individuals by phone to survey about the service provided by ABA Bank.<br>\r\n	- Deliver prepared sales scripts to persuade potential customers to purchase a product or service if you are asked.<br>\r\n	- Describe products and services, respond to questions, identify for the opportunity for sales, obtain customer information, and refer sales opportunity to Relationship ---- Manager/ Consultant.<br>\r\n	- Data entry and maintenance of customer/potential customer data bases.<br>\r\n	- Follow‐up on initial contacts.<br>\r\n	- Maintain records of telephonic interactions, orders and accounts.<br>\r\n	- Keep a close eye on your local competitors &ndash; what they do and how they perform. Plan to gain market share.<br>\r\n	Keep up to date with ABA&rsquo;s products suite and marketing campaigns to ensure superior product knowledge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;\r\n				<table>\r\n					<tbody>\r\n						<tr>\r\n							<td>-&nbsp;Organizational and time management skills.<br>\r\n								- Ability to work effectively in a team environment.<br>\r\n								- Sound written and verbal communication skills.<br>\r\n								- High degree of self‐motivation and excellent interpersonal skills.<br>\r\n								- Computer literacy.<br>\r\n								- Understanding of basic banking products and services.<br>\r\n								- Practical knowledge of operating risk and compliance policies and procedures.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.</td>\r\n						</tr>\r\n					</tbody>\r\n				</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'HR Department Office', '855 98 630 108', 'recruitment@ababank.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(305, 'JOB-305', 148, 23, 29, 9, 24, 4, 2, 7, 'Client Service Advisor', '2', '.', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-01', '2017-03-24 17:11:52', '<p>**&nbsp;Job Description<br>\r\n	Client Service Advisor is responsible for supporting Relationship Managers (RM) functions, and conducting in-house sales activities by exploring client&rsquo;s stated and unstated needs and recommending the right solution, as well as maintenance of accounts and filing.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Location<br>\r\n	- Provincial and Phnom Penh branches<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Duties and Responsibilities<br>\r\n	- Identify and action on sales opportunity for new business opportunity by responding to inquiries from both new and existing customers.<br>\r\n	- Provide consultative service in regard to banking products and services which is considered as a good solution to suite the clients&rsquo; needs.<br>\r\n	- Assist in opening account in system per request from RM or Customers.<br>\r\n	- Making sure that the documents submitted are accurate and valid.<br>\r\n	- Take action to follow up in case provided documents are not complete.<br>\r\n	- Contribute to the development of sound profitable business by creating effective referral networks, including internal business relationship and existing customers in order to achieve the targets.<br>\r\n	- Ensure the compliance with ABA&rsquo;s internal policies, processes &amp; procedure, core values, and code of conducts, etc. are maintained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;\r\n				<table>\r\n					<tbody>\r\n						<tr>\r\n							<td>-&nbsp;Bachelor degree in Business, Finance or Marketing field.<br>\r\n								- Minimum 2 years working experience in sales &amp; marketing.<br>\r\n								- Negotiation and internal relationship building.<br>\r\n								- Organizational and time management skills.Ability to work effectively in a team environment.<br>\r\n								- Competent in spoken and written English communication.<br>\r\n								- Computer literacy.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.</td>\r\n						</tr>\r\n					</tbody>\r\n				</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'HR Department Office', '855 98 630 108', 'recruitment@ababank.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(306, 'JOB-306', 148, 23, 37, 9, 24, 4, 2, 7, 'Teller', '1', '.', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-01', '2017-03-24 17:13:21', '<p>**&nbsp;Job Description<br>\r\n	Teller is responsible for handling customer transactions at banks, including taking deposits, disbursing cash, opening accounts, and investigating fees.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Location<br>\r\n	Provincial and Phnom Penh branches<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Counter operations.<br>\r\n	- Handle cash for all the transactions.<br>\r\n	- Money counterfeit notice.<br>\r\n	- Deposit/withdraw Cash and Cheque.<br>\r\n	- Be Confidential with the Customers&rsquo; balance or other transactions.<br>\r\n	- Exchange money.<br>\r\n	- Printing Bank statement.<br>\r\n	- Closing Account.<br>\r\n	- Provide a comfortable way for customers with the bank services.<br>\r\n	- Check the closed balance with cash on daily basis.</p>\r\n', '<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;\r\n				<table>\r\n					<tbody>\r\n						<tr>\r\n							<td>-&nbsp;Bachelor Degree in Finance, Accounting or other relevant fields.<br>\r\n								- Minimum 1 year experience of relevant experiences in customer services or other front line role.<br>\r\n								- Ability to accurately and efficiently process cash transaction.<br>\r\n								- Attention to details.<br>\r\n								- Good planning, problem solving &amp; organizing skills.<br>\r\n								- Computer skills in Ms Word, Excel, PowerPoint, etc.<br>\r\n								- Good command in spoken and written English is required.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.</td>\r\n						</tr>\r\n					</tbody>\r\n				</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'HR Department Office', '855 98 630 108', 'recruitment@ababank.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(307, 'JOB-307', 148, 23, 37, 9, 24, 4, 2, 7, 'Micro Business Loan Officer', '1', '.', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-01', '2017-03-24 17:16:55', '<p>**&nbsp;Job Description<br>\r\n	Micro Business Loan Officer is responsible for processing and analyzing Micro Business Loan applications and conduct credit investigations, reports and more.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Location<br>\r\n	Provincial and Phnom Penh branches<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Duties and Responsibilities<br>\r\n	- Solicits potential and existing clients in accordance with the guidelines stated in the micro business loan policies and procedures.<br>\r\n	- Analyze and interpret financial statements of the business in order to access the repayment capacity and financial soundness of the borrower.<br>\r\n	- Receives and screens loan applications.<br>\r\n	- Conducts credit investigation for borrowers and their co-makers.<br>\r\n	- Evaluates cash flow of loan applicants.<br>\r\n	- Conducts sit visit of secure collateral.<br>\r\n	- Ascertains the completeness of loan documents.<br>\r\n	- Follows up delinquent clients immediately and refers to immediate supervisor.<br>\r\n	- Recommends remedial measures for delinquent clients in accordance with the recovery policies and procedures of the Bank.<br>\r\n	- Responsible for the attainment of his/her performance targets.</p>\r\n', '<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;\r\n				<table>\r\n					<tbody>\r\n						<tr>\r\n							<td>-&nbsp;&nbsp;Bachelor with major in Banking and Finance, Accounting, - - - Management and Marketing or related field.<br>\r\n								- At least one year experience in Micro Finance&nbsp;<br>\r\n								Institution/commercial bank or related field.<br>\r\n								- English Proficiency.<br>\r\n								- Good level of computer program (MS Word &amp; Excel).<br>\r\n								- Good understanding of business process.<br>\r\n								- Hardworking, commitment, ability to communicate and self-motivated person.<br>\r\n								- Good interpersonal skills.<br>\r\n								- Attention to details.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.</td>\r\n						</tr>\r\n					</tbody>\r\n				</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'HR Department Office', '855 98 630 108', 'recruitment@ababank.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(308, 'JOB-308', 148, 23, 34, 9, 24, 4, 2, 7, 'Physical Cash Management Officer ( 1 Post-Head Office)', '1', '1', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-01', '2017-03-24 17:19:07', '<p>**&nbsp;Job Description:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	S/he is responsible for managing and implementing tasks, in efficient and effective ways, as assigned in the physical cash management unit, treasury department, Advanced Bank of Asia Ltd. and ensures the implementation is in accordance with the operating manuals and procedures.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Location: Head Office<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Duties and Responsibilities:<br>\r\n	- Assist branches in preparing the cash flow projection and control to find out the cash requirement, shortage and surplus in order to take effective and prompt action.<br>\r\n	- Monitor and manage vault cash/nostro account of all ABA Bank&#39;s branches, on daily basis, to see if the balance is over/under limitation and take actions in accordance with procedure.&ensp;&ensp;<br>\r\n	- Monitor and analyze the branches&#39; current cash/nostro against cash flow projection and recommend for cash transfer in/out to ensure sufficient balance for operation and avoid much cash shortage or surplus. In case of shortage or surplus, must promptly report to line manager.<br>\r\n	- Check the fund transfer request from the branches and communicate to line manager or relevant division.<br>\r\n	- Check the request from branches on keeping over-limit balance of cash/nostro account at branches and verify rationales.<br>\r\n	- Prepare reports assigned by line manager and ensure accuracy before submission.<br>\r\n	- Manage and keep all reports and related documents properly and safely in accordance with procedure.<br>\r\n	- Regularly survey challenges faced by the branches, analyze and recommend to line manager for any possible solutions.</p>\r\n', '<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;\r\n				<table>\r\n					<tbody>\r\n						<tr>\r\n							<td>-&nbsp;&nbsp;Bachelor Degree in Accounting/Finance or related fields.<br>\r\n								- At least 1 year of treasury experience especially dealing with cash management in bank or MFI.<br>\r\n								- Having some ideas on analysis of financial and economic data.<br>\r\n								- Be able to meet provided deadline for assigned tasks.<br>\r\n								- Good communication, presentation and interpersonal skills.<br>\r\n								- Computer literacy in MS Word &amp; MS Excel.<br>\r\n								- Honest and reliable person.</td>\r\n						</tr>\r\n					</tbody>\r\n				</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'HR Department Office', '855 98 630 108', 'recruitment@ababank.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(309, 'JOB-309', 148, 23, 45, 9, 24, 4, 2, 7, 'Network Administrator', '2', '1', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-06', '2017-03-24 17:22:10', '<p>**&nbsp;Job Description<br>\r\n	S/he is responsible for maintaining the stable connectivity of bank&#39;s network including but not limited to network configuration, maintenance and troubleshooting. On top of that he is accountable for keeping bank&rsquo;s network secure by complying network security policies.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Location<br>\r\n	Head Office, Phnom Penh&nbsp;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	** Duties and Responsibilities&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Manage, control and troubleshoot LAN, WAN, VPN, Remote -Access and Wifi connection.<br>\r\n	- Install, configure, and troubleshoot network devices - (switch, router, modem, ASA, watchguard, firewalls, load balancing and other network equipment).<br>\r\n	- Monitor network performance and timely troubleshooting of the network (ISP links, branch links, internal network links...etc).<br>\r\n	- Create and maintain documentation, procedure and guideline.<br>\r\n	- Manage and monitor branches connections.<br>\r\n	- Keep up to date IT network infrastructure diagram.</p>\r\n', '<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;\r\n				<table>\r\n					<tbody>\r\n						<tr>\r\n							<td>-&nbsp;Bachelor degree of IT, Computer Science or other related field.<br>\r\n								- At least 2 year experience in IT Network, Technical Support in Bank/MFI or ISP is preferable.<br>\r\n								- Holding any IT Network (CCNA/ CCNP) related training certification is plus.<br>\r\n								- NAT, PAT, Static NAT(Port Forwarding),High Ability with VRRP, and Load Balancing technique.<br>\r\n								- Problem diagnosis, troubleshooting and resolution skill.<br>\r\n								- TCP/IP knowledge and with the ability to troubleshoot system network connectivity related issue.<br>\r\n								- Flexible, honest, quick learner, hard-working, good team work.<br>\r\n								- Willing to learn new technology and more self-motivation and self-study.<br>\r\n								- Good English and Khmer communication (both written and spoken).<br>\r\n								- Able to solve problem independently.<br>\r\n								<br>\r\n								** How to apply<br>\r\n								Interested and qualified applicants should submit only their updated covering letter and CV stating the position you apply for with current photo (4x6) via the Application form below.</td>\r\n						</tr>\r\n					</tbody>\r\n				</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-24', '2017-04-23', 'HR Department Office', '855 98 630 108', 'recruitment@ababank.com', NULL, 1, 1),
(316, 'JOB-316', 22, 44, 28, 9, 38, 3, 2, 7, 'Sales Supervisor', '3', '.', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Good   ', '2017-04-01', '2017-03-28 14:43:46', '<p>JOB TITLE : Sales Supervisor&nbsp;<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Senior Business Development Manager<br>\r\n	DEPARTMENT : Sales and Distribution<br>\r\n	LOCATION : Rattanakiri<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	JOB PURPOSE<br>\r\n	.Meet all the deadlines and requirements of individual/ team assignments and projects<br>\r\n	.Due to the nature of this job, the incumbent will play as a representative of company. He therefore must:<br>\r\n	.Demonstrate high level of integrity, courtesy, self discipline, and professionalism<br>\r\n	+Be confident and mature with positive attitude<br>\r\n	+Be respectful<br>\r\n	+Be always caring and understanding.<br>\r\n	+Be able to handle effectively all queries in professional manner<br>\r\n	.Build effective relationships both within and outside the department; seek input from and maintain effective ongoing communication with others<br>\r\n	.Dress always attitude<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	PRINCIPLE ACCOUNTABILITY<br>\r\n	.Responsible for assigned monthly APE and Policy target and year-end target of APE and Policy.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	.Financial Consultants performance monitoring.<br>\r\n	.Provide immediate support to Financial Consultant in customer handling<br>\r\n	.Review the area management KPIs and take necessary actions to achieve the target KPIs.<br>\r\n	.Keep coaching and training Financial Consultant to understand all our products and services<br>\r\n	.Build intimacy with branch manager and management team of ACLEDA Branches.<br>\r\n	.Prepare and implement monthly activities including customer presentation and joint visit with Financial Consultant.<br>\r\n	.Liaise with other departments on matters relating to daily sales activities.<br>\r\n	.Perform other duties/target as assigned by Head of Bancassurance or Director of Sales and Marketing</p>\r\n', '<p>REQUIREMENT<br>\r\n	.A College degree in business administration majoring in marketing, or business related field.<br>\r\n	.A minimum of 2 year experience in a supervisory position in Customer Service or Sales<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	DESIRABLE<br>\r\n	.Ability to manage and work independently.<br>\r\n	.Ability to think creatively and take initiative.<br>\r\n	.Analytical skills and demonstrate positive attitude<br>\r\n	.Excellent business communication skills, commendable in English language both in speaking and writing.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	.Computer literacy in Microsoft offices applications.</p>\r\n', '', 0, 1, '2017-03-28', '2017-04-27', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', NULL, 1, 1),
(317, 'JOB-317', 22, 44, 28, 9, 45, 3, 2, 7, 'Financial Consultant (formerly Life Insurance Specialist)', '.', '13', 2, '.', 'Bachelor Degree', 'English-- Fair   ', '2017-04-01', '2017-03-28 14:49:52', '<p>JOB TITLE : Financial Consultant<br>\r\n	REPORTING TO : Senior Business Development Manager<br>\r\n	DEPARTMENT : Sales and Distributions<br>\r\n	LOCATION :<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Phnom Penh<br>\r\n	Ang Snoul<br>\r\n	Pursat<br>\r\n	Kompong Speu<br>\r\n	Svay Rieng<br>\r\n	Prey Veng<br>\r\n	Poipet<br>\r\n	Koh Kong<br>\r\n	Kratie<br>\r\n	Rattanak Kiri<br>\r\n	Steung Trang<br>\r\n	Preah Vihear<br>\r\n	Pouk<br>\r\n	Bakan<br>\r\n	Bati<br>\r\n	Koh Thom<br>\r\n	Batheay<br>\r\n	Stoung<br>\r\n	Sreisonthor<br>\r\n	Steung Treng<br>\r\n	Bavel<br>\r\n	Mongkol Borei<br>\r\n	Anglong Veng<br>\r\n	Basdth<br>\r\n	Pea Reang<br>\r\n	Kompong Trach<br>\r\n	Kampot-Kep<br>\r\n	Kompong Thom<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Job Responsibilities:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Approach potential customers from the customer contact list and referrals provided by a distribution partner&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Present and provide consultation with regards to the life insurance products to all prospected customers and then sell the products as per the needs of such customers<br>\r\n	- Assist the customers by providing them after sales service and information as and when required by such customers&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Work with the Senior Sales Supervisor in providing the regular sales reports as per the Company policies<br>\r\n	- Perform other tasks as required by Supervisor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>REQUIREMENT<br>\r\n	.A College degree in business administration majoring in marketing, or business related field.<br>\r\n	.A minimum of 2 year experience in a supervisory position in Customer Service or Sales<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	DESIRABLE<br>\r\n	.Ability to manage and work independently.<br>\r\n	.Ability to think creatively and take initiative.<br>\r\n	.Analytical skills and demonstrate positive attitude<br>\r\n	.Excellent business communication skills, commendable in English language both in speaking and writing.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	.Computer literacy in Microsoft offices applications.</p>\r\n', '<p>Key Success Factors:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Graduates, from University/College, an advantage.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Fresh graduates with high academic credentials shall be considered, though a field in sales, marketing, banking and finance are preferable.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Experience in sales of 6 &ndash; 12 months would be advantageous&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Result &ndash;oriented, committed, flexibility, and self- driven individuals<br>\r\n	- Good communication skills &amp; negotiation skills<br>\r\n	- Enjoy meeting new people and good relationship management&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Basic computer literacy (MS Word/Excel, Internet, E-mail) is essential<br>\r\n	- Good English would be an additional advantage.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	The Company offers a competitive remuneration package and attractive long term career prospect and a professional, transparent, and exciting environment.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	If you&rsquo;re interested and think you&rsquo;re the right person, please submit your CV with cover letter and a recent photo (4x6) to HR Department by using the contact detail below:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Website: www.prudential.com.kh&nbsp;<br>\r\n	Email: pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	Cc: rathana.hout@prudential.com.kh;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Phone: 023 964 555<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Deadline: No later than 06 April, 2017 at 5:30PM<br>\r\n	Women and the disabled are encouraged to apply. Only short-listed candidates will be notified for interview. Received applications will not be returned.<br>\r\n	Notes: Certificates and supporting documents attached should be brought along when you are invited for interview.<br>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 0, 1, '2017-03-28', '2017-04-27', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', '3', 1, 1),
(318, 'JOB-318', 22, 44, 62, 9, 45, 3, 2, 7, 'Supervisor – Legal & Corporate Integrity', '.', '13', 2, '.', '.', '.', '2017-04-27', '2017-03-28 14:53:37', '<p>Direct Reporting Line: Senor Supervisor-Legal and Corporate Integrity<br>\r\n	Department/Function: Finance<br>\r\n	Work Location: Phnom Penh, Cambodia<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Principle Accountabilities:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Assist to develop the policy and Standard of Procedures to be in line with Group, Regional, and other applicable regulatory requirements, to cover money laundering deterrence issues, to protect the good reputation of the Group and avoid criminal and civil sanctions against the company, or its employees including analyzing and quarterly updating AML risk assessment;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Administer Customer Risk Classification System where this role will capture customers with higher risk profile in respect of money laundering, terrorism financing and sanctions so that business can be proceed per business as usual in accordance with Group, Regional Head Office, and PCLA risk appetite;<br>\r\n	&bull; Source independent information to build up case for verification of alerts from Sanctions Screening which provide significant supports to Operations, in particular New Business and Underwriting, through fast tracking the turnaround time for policy issuance;<br>\r\n	&bull; Clear initial screening and monthly screening alerts and provide the related assistance to other departments on as needed basis;<br>\r\n	&bull; Report the Suspicious Transaction Reporting (&ldquo;STR&rdquo;) and Cash Transaction Reporting (&ldquo;CTR&rdquo;) to Cambodian Financial Intelligence Unit (&ldquo;CAFIU&rdquo;). STR and CTR are required every two (02) weeks to ensure that the business is conducted in compliance with the local requirements;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Update Local Political Exposed Persons List and Local Sanction List;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Evaluate new products and services to determine the level of risk 1) conduct the new customer by KYC/CDD before acceptance; 2) Evaluate the risk assessment of customers by level of risks; 3) Monitor the existing customers regularly;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Prepare and submit reports as required under local regulations and PCA/Group standards such as AML Quarterly Report and AML Annual Risk Assessment;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	&bull; Monitor transactions and prepare suspicious transactions report as per company policy<br>\r\n	&bull; Conduct standard monitoring and special monitoring as required per plan<br>\r\n	&bull; Work with IT Department to enhance &amp; develop the AML Profiling in in Life Asia System as per compliance plan<br>\r\n	&bull; Prepare the recommendation and report re the result of AML screening for MLPO review and sign-off<br>\r\n	&bull; Be a contact person with AML Regional Team and prepare and update policies and procedures based on updated Group and Regional policy and disseminate information to the relevant personnel, can be through email or training<br>\r\n	&bull; Oversee administrative matters related to and compliance with anti-money laundering and terrorist financing activities<br>\r\n	&bull; Develop quality assurance (QA) review template and perform QA review according to the approved annual work plans to ensure procedures and policies are effectively implemented<br>\r\n	&bull; Follow up the QA findings in regular basis to ensure the compliance risk can be closed in timeliness by tracking report<br>\r\n	&bull; Be a contact person/coordinator with Regional AML/GWIA team when they conduct QA review/audit review<br>\r\n	&bull; Changing the attitudes of management &amp; staff in relation to AML &amp; CFT<br>\r\n	&bull; Be able to identify and assess AML/CFT related risks as per business scope<br>\r\n	&bull; Develop &amp; review AML Training Materials (induction training) either through video training, CBT platform, or face to face training and make sure the training material is up to date based on the revised policies<br>\r\n	&bull; Provide necessary AML training whenever required<br>\r\n	&bull; Be a helpful assistant/adviser re AML matters to all functions in the Company whenever the help is needed<br>\r\n	&bull; If required, cooperate with internal investigator (local or regional level), to investigate all AML related cases</p>\r\n', '<p>Qualification:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- University graduated, major in Law, Economics, Business Administration, Accounting, or Finance&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Experience in legal, compliance, finance, banking, auditing, distribution channel or equivalents is desired&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Possess Research Skills, Reporting Research Results, Analyzing Information, Coordination, Administrative Writing Skills, and Organization, Working with others, Audit, General Math Skills, And Statistical Analysis.<br>\r\n	- Excellent spoken and written English<br>\r\n	- At least four years of relevant experiences<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Desirable:<br>\r\n	- Has a strong ability to apply logical and critical thinking to resolve problems<br>\r\n	- Propensity to plan strategically yet be able to adapt quickly to reality&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Strong analytical skills<br>\r\n	- Strong numerical, written, and verbal communication skills<br>\r\n	- Ability to build trust and rapport with all levels of the organization<br>\r\n	- Good communication &amp; strong commitment in performing all tasks</p>\r\n', '<p>Key Success Factors:<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	- Graduates, from University/College, an advantage.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Fresh graduates with high academic credentials shall be considered, though a field in sales, marketing, banking and finance are preferable.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Experience in sales of 6 &ndash; 12 months would be advantageous&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Result &ndash;oriented, committed, flexibility, and self- driven individuals<br>\r\n	- Good communication skills &amp; negotiation skills<br>\r\n	- Enjoy meeting new people and good relationship management&nbsp;<br>\r\n	- Basic computer literacy (MS Word/Excel, Internet, E-mail) is essential<br>\r\n	- Good English would be an additional advantage.&nbsp;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	The Company offers a competitive remuneration package and attractive long term career prospect and a professional, transparent, and exciting environment.<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	If you&rsquo;re interested and think you&rsquo;re the right person, please submit your CV with cover letter and a recent photo (4x6) to HR Department by using the contact detail below:&nbsp;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Website: www.prudential.com.kh&nbsp;<br>\r\n	Email: pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh;&nbsp;<br>\r\n	Cc: rathana.hout@prudential.com.kh;<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Phone: 023 964 555<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n	Deadline: No later than 06 April, 2017 at 5:30PM<br>\r\n	Women and the disabled are encouraged to apply. Only short-listed candidates will be notified for interview. Received applications will not be returned.<br>\r\n	Notes: Certificates and supporting documents attached should be brought along when you are invited for interview.<br>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 0, 1, '2017-03-28', '2017-04-27', 'HR Department', '(855) 23 964 555', 'pclarecruitment@prudential.com.kh', '3', 1, 1),
